<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="cat-page-faq">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="cat-page-faq-head">
      <span class="eyebrow">Frequently asked questions</span>
      <h2>What we get asked most about lash extensions & semi-permanent make-up.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="cat-page-faq-list">
      <div class="cat-page-faq-item open">
        <button class="cat-page-faq-q" type="button">How long do individual lash extensions last? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="cat-page-faq-a"><p>Between 3 and 4 weeks, depending on your natural lash cycle. We schedule a top-up every 3-4 weeks to keep volume consistent. No damage to your natural lashes.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cat-page-faq-item">
        <button class="cat-page-faq-q" type="button">Does semi-permanent make-up hurt? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="cat-page-faq-a"><p>Mild discomfort, not pain. We apply numbing cream before and during the session. Most patients describe the sensation as a brief tingling or pinch.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cat-page-faq-item">
        <button class="cat-page-faq-q" type="button">When should I have my semi-permanent make-up touched up? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="cat-page-faq-a"><p>Initial top-up at 4-6 weeks (after the healing process) to refine the result. After that, annual top-ups to maintain colour and intensity.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cat-page-faq-item">
        <button class="cat-page-faq-q" type="button">Allergies? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="cat-page-faq-a"><p>Hypoallergenic pigments, but we always run an allergy patch test on a small area beforehand. If you react, we don't apply.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cat-page-faq-item">
        <button class="cat-page-faq-q" type="button">Can I exercise / sunbathe afterwards? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="cat-page-faq-a"><p>After the session: 7 days with no direct sun, no saunas, no sea/pool water and no make-up over the area. After that you can carry on as normal — daily SPF is key for the pigment to last.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

